Checking For Null Values In Train and Test Dataframe

  • isnull() returns boolean values which contains True for NaN value and False for Not Null value
  • any() checks any missing value in any column
  • describe() gives a summary:
    • count : 785, which indicates the number of columns in the train_data
    • unique : 1, which indicates there is one unique value acoross all the 785 columns
    • top : False, which indicates the unique value is False
    • freq : 785, which indicates the False appears in the 785 columns
  • Missing values have been checked for both in the Train and Test dataframe. There is no missing value in the Train and Test dataframe.

Convolution Process

Max Pooling Process

CNN Architecture

CNN Architecture:

  • Sequential model
  • Convolution layer with 32 different filters each of size (5,5). Padding same means output images size is same as input image size. Relu activation function has been used. This layer will generate 32 feature maps for each image.
  • Adding another convolution layer with the same configuration.
  • Add a Max pooling layer of size (2,2) and strides=2, padding=valid means no padding. The image size will shrink.
  • Add a dropout layer of rate 0.25 to avoid overfitting.
  • Convolution layer with 64 different filters each of size (3,3). Padding same means output images size is same as input image size. Relu activation function has been used. This layer will generate 64 feature maps for each image.
  • Adding another convolution layer with the same configuration.
  • Add a Max pooling layer of size (2,2) and strides=2, padding=valid means no padding. The image size will shrink.
  • Add a dropout layer of rate 0.25 to avoid overfitting.
  • Add a flatten layer
  • Add a Dense layer of 256 neuron
  • Add a Dropout layer of rate 0.5
  • Add a Dense layer of 10 neuron with Softmax
In [45]:
xxxxxxxxxx
 
np.random.seed(42)
tf.random.set_seed(42)
# Kaggle
model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(filters = 32, kernel_size = 5,padding = 'Same', 
                 activation ='relu', input_shape = (28,28,1)))
model.add(Conv2D(filters = 32, kernel_size = 5,padding = 'Same', 
                 activation ='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=2, strides=2, padding='valid'))
model.add(Dropout(0.25))
model.add(Conv2D(filters = 64, kernel_size = 3,padding = 'Same', 
                 activation ='relu'))
model.add(Conv2D(filters = 64, kernel_size = 3,padding = 'Same', 
                 activation ='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=2, strides=2, padding='valid'))
model.add(Dropout(0.25))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(256, activation = "relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(10, activation = "softmax"))
